    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-11-07T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-11-07T22:00:00-05:00" n="425"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d425">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/25297a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in France (<persName type="to">Tuck</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-07T23:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 7, 1942—11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>685. Personal for the Chargé d’Affaires. Report to the Department immediately
                    upon delivery to Marshal Pétain<note n="49" xml:id="d425fn49">Marshal Henri
                        Philippe Pétain, French Chief of State.</note> of the unenciphered <pb
                        facs="0436" n="430" xml:id="pg_430"/> message<note n="50" xml:id="d425fn50"
                        >Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, November 14, 1942, p.
                        904.</note> which you have received for him from the President.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
